.TH QDDIFF 1 "2026-05-02" "smartmet-qdtools" "SmartMet Tools"
.SH NAME
qddiff \- extract the differences between two querydata files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B qddiff
.RI [ options ]
.I inputfile1 inputfile2 outputfile
.br
.B qddiff
.RI [ options ]
.I inputdir outputfile
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B qddiff
writes a querydata file containing the differences between two inputs.
The second form is equivalent to the first with the second-newest file
in
.I inputdir
substituted for
.I inputfile1
and the newest file substituted for
.IR inputfile2 .
.PP
For numerical differences between fields, see
.BR qddifference (1).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h
Print the help message.
.TP
.B \-t
Extract only new time steps.
.TP
.B \-p
Extract only common times whose parameter values changed.
.TP
.B \-v
Verbose mode.
.TP
.B \-V
Very verbose mode; prints an analysis of the differences.
.TP
.B \-d
Debug mode (implies verbose).
.SH EXAMPLES
Diff the two newest files in a forecast history directory:
.PP
.RS 4
qddiff /data/forecast/history changes.sqd
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR qddifference (1),
.BR qdcombine (1),
.BR qdinfo (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Finnish Meteorological Institute
.PP
